    "description": "<p>The reverse of <em>Raise Dead Fully</em>, this spell destroys living creatures the same way the normal version destroys undead.</p>\n                      <p><strong>Effects on Living Creatures:</strong></p>\n                      <ul>\n                        <li><strong>7 HD or less:</strong> The target is immediately slain (no saving throw).</li>\n                        <li><strong>7-12 HD:</strong> The target must make a saving throw vs. spells at <strong>-4 penalty</strong>; failure results in instant death.</li>\n                        <li><strong>12+ HD:</strong> The target takes [[/r 6d10 #damage]] damage; a successful saving throw vs. spells reduces damage by half.</li>\n                      </ul>\n                      <p><strong>Effects on Undead:</strong> This spell has the same effect as <em>Cureall</em> would on a living creature:</p>\n                      <ul>\n                        <li>Heals the undead to full hit points, leaving only [[/r 1d6 #damage]] remaining.</li>\n                        <li>Can remove afflictions such as blindness, disease, feeblemind, or paralysis.</li>\n                      </ul>",
